 {"id":"beads_rust-1jcq","title":"Implement syntax highlighting for code blocks","description":"## Feature: Code Syntax Highlighting

### Purpose
When issue descriptions or comments contain code blocks, render them with syntax highlighting for improved readability.

### File Location
`src/format/syntax.rs`

### CRITICAL: Mode Behavior
Syntax highlighting ONLY in Rich mode:
- Rich: Full color syntax highlighting
- Plain: Code block with no colors (indented or fenced)
- JSON: Raw code string unchanged
- Quiet: No output

### Implementation

```rust
use rich_rust::syntax::Syntax;
use crate::format::OutputContext;

pub fn highlight_code(code: &str, language: &str, ctx: &OutputContext) -> String {
    if !ctx.is_rich() {
        // Plain mode: return indented code block
        return code.lines()
            .map(|l| format!("    {}", l))
            .collect::<Vec<_>>()
            .join("\n");
    }

    let syntax = Syntax::new(code, language)
        .with_line_numbers(code.lines().count() > 5)
        .with_theme("monokai")
        .with_word_wrap(ctx.width());

    syntax.render()
}
```

### Language Detection
1. Explicit fencing: ```rust
2. Filename hint: `main.rs`
3. Heuristics for common patterns
4. Default to "text" if unknown

### Supported Languages (Priority Order)
- rust, go, python, typescript, javascript
- sql, bash, yaml, json, toml
- html, css, markdown
- Others via syntect

---

