 {"id":"beads_rust-36dk","title":"Implement IssueTable component","description":"### Purpose
The IssueTable is THE most frequently rendered component in br - it powers the `list`, `search`, `ready`, `blocked`, `stale`, and `orphans` commands.

### File Location
`src/format/components/issue_table.rs` (NOT src/output/)

### CRITICAL: Integration with Existing Code
Must integrate with existing patterns in `src/format/text.rs`:
- Use same color mappings (format_status, format_priority, format_type)
- Use `terminal_width()` function
- Use `truncate_title()` function

### API Design
```rust
use crate::format::{OutputContext, Theme};
use crate::format::text::{terminal_width, truncate_title};

pub struct IssueTable<'a> {
    issues: &'a [Issue],
    columns: Vec<TableColumn>,
    ctx: &'a OutputContext,
    show_deps: bool,
    highlight_ready: bool,
}

impl<'a> IssueTable<'a> {
    pub fn new(issues: &'a [Issue], ctx: &'a OutputContext) -> Self;
    pub fn columns(mut self, cols: &[&str]) -> Self;
    pub fn show_dependencies(mut self, show: bool) -> Self;
    pub fn highlight_ready(mut self, highlight: bool) -> Self;
    pub fn render(&self) -> Result<()>;
}
```

### Column Types
- ID: Left-aligned, dimmed prefix, bold number
- Title: Left-aligned, truncated with ellipsis (use existing truncate_title)
- Status: Centered, colored pill (use Theme::status_style)
- Priority: Centered, heat-map colored (use Theme::priority_style)
- Type: Centered, icon + colored text (use Theme::type_style)
- Labels: Left-aligned, comma-separated colored chips
- Assignee: Left-aligned, @ prefix
- Created/Updated: Right-aligned, relative time

### Mode Behavior
- Rich: Full table with colors, borders (Box::ROUNDED), proper alignment
- Plain: ASCII table (Box::ASCII), no colors
- JSON: Return structured data, no table rendering
- Quiet: Skip entirely

